text: 191 North Wacker is a 516ft (157m) tall skyscraper in Chicago, Illinois. The construction was from 2000 to 2002. It has 37 floors, 14 elevators, and 68,184 mÂ² of floor space. Kohn Pedersen Fox Associates designed the building.
